Note:
Unit tests for compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/blake3.runa.

Test vectors are the official BLAKE3 test vectors:
  https://github.com/BLAKE3-team/BLAKE3/blob/master/test_vectors/test_vectors.json

Input pattern: byte_i = i mod 251 for i = 0..length-1.
Tested lengths: 0, 1, 64, 65, 127, 128, 1024, 1025, 8192.
For each length: default hash, keyed_hash with key
"whats the Elvish word for friend", derive_key with context
"BLAKE3 2019-12-27 16:29:52 test vectors context".

Plus one XOF test (1024-byte input, 131-byte output).
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/blake3.runa" as Blake3

Process called "fill_input_pattern" takes buf as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let val be i modulo by 251
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, i, val)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

