Process called "test_blake3_L8192" that takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    T.begin_suite(results, "blake3 official vectors len=8192")

    Note: 8KB input drives ~144KB of per-call scratch through the tree, and the
    Note: suite chains hash + keyed_hash + derive_key on the same arena (without
    Note: reset). Allocate 768KB to keep all three calls within the same arena.
    Let arena be Arena.arena_create(786432)
    T.assert_not_null(results, "arena created", arena)

    Let inp be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 8192)
    T.assert_not_null(results, "input allocated", inp)
    fill_input_pattern(inp, 8192)

    Let digest be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    Let rc be Blake3.blake3_hash(arena, inp, 8192, digest)
    T.assert_equal(results, "blake3_hash returned 1", rc, 1)
    Let h0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(digest, 0)
    T.assert_equal(results, "L8192 hash byte 0", h0, 170)
